Rocket launcher tube found on front lawn of Jersey City, New Jersey, home. 20-year-old AT4 anti-tank rocket launcher tube is a one-time-use device. launcher "is no longer operable and not considered to be a hazard to public safety," police say.
Police defuse a bomb consisting of 200 liters of fuel, gas cylinders and nails. A second car packed with gas and nails was later found to have been parked. Two weeks after the deadly 7/7 bombings, four men are alleged to have attempted to carry out a second wave of attacks.
NEW: About 2,000 customers without power. Quake centered about two miles east-northeast of Oakland, at a depth of 3.6 miles. Oakland is just east of San Francisco, across San Francisco Bay. The shaking lasted about 50 seconds, CNN meteorologist Chad Myers says.
At least 14 killed, 60 others wounded in attack in Batna, east of Algiers, Algeria. Bomb went off 15 minutes before expected arrival of President Abdel-Aziz Bouteflika. Algeria faces a continuing Islamic insurgency, according to the CIA.
Virus found in healthy Australian honey bees may be playing a role in U.S. colony collapse. Colony collapse disorder has killed millions of bees, imperiling crops. Virus identified in the healthy Australian bees is Israeli Acute Paralysis Virus (IAPV) Although worker bees in colony collapse disorder vanish, bees infected with IAPV die.
NEW: Vice President Dick Cheney will serve as acting president briefly. NEW: Bush's last colonoscopy was in June 2002, and no abnormalities were found. The president's doctor had recommended a repeat procedure in about five years. Colonoscopy is most sensitive test for colon cancer, rectal cancer and polyps.
Savers at leading UK mortgage bank line up for second day to empty accounts. Northern Rock was bailed out by the Bank of England after slashing profit forecasts. Shares in Northern Rock dropped up to 30 percent in Friday trading. British Bankers' Association has urged customers to "calm down"
Beckham has begun a five-year contract with the Los Angeles Galaxy team. CNN looks at how Bekham fulfilled his dream of playing for Manchester United. The road to major league football in the U.S. is a well-worn route for some of world's greatest players.
Carlos Alberto has joined Werder Bremen for a club record fee of $10.7 million. The 22-year-old scored in FC Porto's Champions League final victory in 2004. He is the third top Brazilian player to join the German league in three days.
Lohan fans have little to fear because no actor is uninsurable, say underwriting experts. Unless an actor is serving time in prison, even the most volatile can be covered. Insurance rates for errant actors can range from 1 percent to 3 percent of a movie's production budget.
