French foreign minister Bernard Kouchner has a reputation for challenging convention. He is a humanitarian as well as a patriot, with a strong commitment to human rights. Washington will have been delighted by his 'get serious' warning to Teheran.
Chelsea are waiting on the fitness of John Terry ahead of Wednesday's Champions League match with Valencia. Center-back Terry suffered a broken cheekbone during Saturday's 0-0 draw with Fulham. Frank Lampard has been ruled out though as the midfielder continues to recover from his thigh injury.
Pentagon preparing new supply routes for troops in Iraq if Turkey cuts off U.S. access. Turkey incensed by resolution calling killing of Armenians by Ottoman Turks genocide. Turkey threatens to block access to Incirlik Air Base after resolution passed House committee. Jordan and Kuwait are among the alternatives the United States is considering.
$2.3 billion was spent on political and issue-advocacy TV commercials in 2006. Costs to produce a TV commercial are no longer prohibitive for local and state candidates. Mitt Romney leads all candidates in TV spending, having aired his commercials more than 11,000 times.
India has elected its first female president, official results show. Pratibha Patil, 72, easily beat opposition-backed challenger Bhairon Singh Shekhawat. Patil won about two thirds of the electoral college votes. Supporters hope Patil's candidacy will help bring issues that plague women into spotlight.
Explorer Dennis Schmitt found an island nearly two years ago near Greenland. Many climatologists and scientists say arctic ice melt is result of global warming. Many global warming experts say phenomenon, if unchecked, is capable of altering world's climate. Other scientists and observers say it is simply the latest shift in cyclical patterns.
